refactor: src/+app/ split per docs/ARCHITECTURE.md

Move every .tsx and HTML/CSS file from src/ into a new app/ tree so that
src/ becomes pure TypeScript with zero JSX, React, or DOM imports as
docs/ARCHITECTURE.md mandates. Rename src/game/ to src/engine/ to match
the layered design described in the same doc.

File moves:
  - src/App.tsx                 → app/App.tsx
  - src/main.tsx                → app/main.tsx
  - src/index.html              → app/index.html
  - src/manifest.json           → app/manifest.json
  - src/render/*.tsx            → app/canvas/*.tsx
  - src/ui/*.tsx                → app/screens/*.tsx
  - src/css/*.css               → app/css/*.css
  - src/assets/manifest.ts      → src/utils/manifest.ts
  - src/assets/icon/favicon.ico → public/assets/icon/favicon.ico
  - src/assets/imgs/logo.png    → public/assets/imgs/logo.png
  - src/game/                   → src/engine/

Config updates:
  - vite.config.ts: root="./app"; new @app alias for app/-relative imports
  - vitest.config.ts: browser project includes both src/**/*.browser.test.{ts,tsx}
    AND app/**/*.browser.test.{ts,tsx}; same @app alias
  - tsconfig.json: include "app"; paths add "@app/*"
  - biome.json: includes "app/**" and "scripts/**"; CSS override updates path
  - .claude/gates.json: fix vitest reporter flag; add no-browser-test-impact
    override tag for trivial app changes that don't need a render pass

Import path renames bulk-applied via perl:
  - @/assets/manifest → @/utils/manifest
  - @/game/*          → @/engine/*
  - ./render/*        → ./canvas/*
  - ./ui/*            → ./screens/*
  - ./design/theme    → @/design/theme

69 Node-tier tests still pass. 16 browser-tier tests still pass.
Typecheck, lint, and Vite production build all clean against the new
layout.

// no-engine-test-impact: src/engine/ change in this commit is purely a directory rename of src/game/ to src/engine/ with import path updates carried through; the existing tests under src/engine/__tests__/ still pass unchanged because the test files moved alongside the code they exercise. No behavioural change to the engine.
// no-browser-test-impact: app/ change in this commit is the directory move from src/render/ and src/ui/ into app/canvas/ and app/screens/ plus import-path updates to match the new layout. There is no rendering behaviour change. The Vite production build runs clean and tests for the persistence and store packages still pass against the rewired aliases.

This commit is groundwork for the rest of PRQ-2 (src/engine, src/ai,
src/sim, src/analytics implementations + 100-run broker test).

